<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF57FF971D95FEA299EAFC8B" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF57FF971D95FEA29A78FD1B" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971D95FEA29974FEDE" bold="true" box="[199,322,294,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Larger (TL: 
<quantity id="664DB6BCBF57FF971C86FEA29A69FEDF" box="[468,607,294,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="5.4" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="5.1">5.1–5.7 mm</quantity>
), oblong-oval species. Head brownish black, usually with reddish clypeus and two oval spots on vertex; pronotum brownish black, laterally broadly testaceous and with testaceous translucent anterior margin; elytra brown with somewhat paler base. Pronotum with only very few short longitudinal strioles laterally. Each elytron with six complete discal striae and one submarginal stria: striae 5–6 beginning slightly posteriorly from base; stria 1 longest, ending close to apex, odd striae somewhat longer than even ones; stria 6 shortest, ending at apical fourth; submarginal stria long, beginning before elytral mid-length and ending at apical fourth (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF971DBEFE7B9907FD87" box="[236,305,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[245,1344,183,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[229,1359,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Habitus of Copelatus in China. 9. C. malaisei (♂; Tengchong, Yunnan); 10. C. malaisei (♀; Tengchong, Yunnan); 11. C. miaowangi sp. nov. (paratype ♂; Liupanshui, Guizhou); 12. C. mopanshanensis sp. nov. (paratype ♂; Mopan Shan, Yunnan). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410708/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view simple, sickle shaped, regularly curved to bluntly pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF971D89FDA79918FDA3" box="[219,302,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–50" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,207,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-18@39.[192,1395,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 39–50. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 39, 41, 43, 45, 47, 49. median lobe in lateral view; 40, 42, 44, 46, 48, 50. paramere. 39–40. C. japonicus (Shanghai); 41. C. malaisei (a. Gaoligongshan, Yunnan; b. Renjiafen, Yunnan); 42. C. malaisei (Renjiafen, Yunnan); 43–44. C. miaowangi sp. nov. (paratype, Liupanshui, Guizhou); 45–46. C. mopanshanensis sp. nov. (holotype, Mopanshan, Yunnan); 47–48. C. nanlingensis sp. nov. (holotype, Dadongshan, Guangdong); 49–50. C. oblitus (Macao). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412781/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Parameres moderately broad, ‘C’-shaped; apex short and broad; apical lobes long, club-shaped (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF97183DFDA79881FDFF" captionStart="FIGURES 39–50" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,207,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-18@39.[192,1395,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 39–50. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 39, 41, 43, 45, 47, 49. median lobe in lateral view; 40, 42, 44, 46, 48, 50. paramere. 39–40. C. japonicus (Shanghai); 41. C. malaisei (a. Gaoligongshan, Yunnan; b. Renjiafen, Yunnan); 42. C. malaisei (Renjiafen, Yunnan); 43–44. C. miaowangi sp. nov. (paratype, Liupanshui, Guizhou); 45–46. C. mopanshanensis sp. nov. (holotype, Mopanshan, Yunnan); 47–48. C. nanlingensis sp. nov. (holotype, Dadongshan, Guangdong); 49–50. C. oblitus (Macao). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412781/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Females dimorphic; striolate form with whole pronotum and elytra except for apex densely covered with short irregular longitudinal strioles (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF971CBFFDEF9A77FD1B" box="[493,577,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[245,1344,183,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[229,1359,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Habitus of Copelatus in China. 9. C. malaisei (♂; Tengchong, Yunnan); 10. C. malaisei (♀; Tengchong, Yunnan); 11. C. miaowangi sp. nov. (paratype ♂; Liupanshui, Guizhou); 12. C. mopanshanensis sp. nov. (paratype ♂; Mopan Shan, Yunnan). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410708/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF57FF971D95FD0A99EAFC8B" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971D95FD0A99ABFD36" bold="true" box="[199,413,654,680]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Collection details.</emphasis>
At the locality Renjiafen, 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF57FF971F94FD0B9B70FD37" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1954" box="[710,838,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971F94FD0B9B70FD37" box="[710,838,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">C. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in ruderal habitat, in a small (diameter ca. 
<quantity id="664DB6BCBF57FF971DEDFD3798DBFD53" box="[191,237,691,717]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
), temporary pool with clayey bottom and dense vegetation; the species was syntopical there, although less abundant, with 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF57FF971C1BFD539A3AFD6F" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,524,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversistriatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971C1BFD539A3AFD6F" box="[329,524,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">C. diversistriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF57FF971F44FD539A59FD6F" box="[534,623,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
In Tengchong, 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF57FF971E76FD539B93FD6F" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1954" box="[804,933,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971E76FD539B93FD6F" box="[804,933,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">C. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in a marsh with dense emergent water macrophytes (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF971C29FD7F99F9FC8B" box="[379,463,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–80" captionStartId="43.[151,264,969,993]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,181,946]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[214,1374,181,946]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 79–80. Habitat of Copelatus in China. 79. Tengchong, Yunnan (C. malaisei); 80. Lantau, Hongkong (C. oblitus and C. sp.)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410790/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF57FF971D95FC9A9B0EFCC3" pageId="10" pageNumber="261" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF57FF971D95FC9A9B0EFCC3" blockId="10.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971D95FC9A9957FCA6" bold="true" box="[199,353,798,824]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species occurring in the northeastern Myanmar (Kachin State) and western 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF57FF9719A1FC9B9D7AFCA7" box="[1267,1356,799,825]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, China (Gaoligong Shan Mts.). 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF57FF971CF5FCC69AF1FCC2" bold="true" box="[423,711,834,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">
First record from 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF57FF971F2CFCC69AF1FCC2" box="[638,711,834,860]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">China</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF57FF971F85FCC79B1CFCC3" box="[727,810,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 81" captionStartId="43.[151,250,2008,2032]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,1062,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-47@43.[224,1364,1054,1983]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 81. Map of distribution of Copelatus in China Mainland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411120" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411120/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="261">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
